## Implementation Plan for Profile Command (Issue #56)

### Goal
Surface CPU profiling data from Sentry via CLI commands.

### Research Findings
- Sentry's profiling API uses Explore Events with dataset=profile_functions for listing
- Flamegraph endpoint: GET /organizations/{org}/profiling/flamegraph/ for detailed analysis
- Found schema patterns in sentry-api-schema and sentry-mcp repositories

### Implementation Approach
1. Types (src/types/profile.ts) - Zod schemas for flamegraph response, profile functions, analysis results
2. API Client - Add getFlamegraph() and listProfiledTransactions() methods
3. Analyzer (src/lib/profile/analyzer.ts) - Hot path detection, percentile calculation, frame analysis
4. Formatters (src/lib/formatters/profile.ts) - Human-readable output for profile data
5. Commands:
   - profile list: Lists transactions with available profile data
   - profile view: Analyzes CPU profile showing hot paths, percentiles, recommendations

### Key Features
- Hot path analysis with CPU time percentages
- P75/P95/P99 percentile statistics
- User code filtering (--all-frames to include library code)
- JSON output for automation
- --web flag to open in Sentry UI
- Configurable time periods (1h/24h/7d/14d/30d)

### Files Created/Modified
- src/types/profile.ts (new)
- src/lib/profile/analyzer.ts (new)
- src/lib/formatters/profile.ts (new)
- src/commands/profile/{index,list,view}.ts (new)
- src/lib/api-client.ts (modified)
- src/lib/sentry-urls.ts (modified)
- src/app.ts (modified)
